			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Selo's Accelerando is a good song... <BR>
but if you use it improperly while in a group, your going to get your friends KILLED!!!<BR>
Ive noticed several times while playing selo with a common hand drum that i was running faster than my party. i messed around and ran backwards (faceing them, but still going in the same direction) and i was STILL going faster than them.... my POINT is that if you dont watch over your party while using this song to flee,you'll majorly out run your group, leaving them in the dust to die. <BR>
so if your going to use this song in a big open area like the commons or karana, autofollow the person leading the group... you'll find you automaticly match the party's rate of movement and wont leave anybody behind(unless their encumbered)...<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Bards are the mortar in the wall that is Norath. If the mortar is shoddy, the wall crumbles... if the mortar is strong, the wall stands tall.<BR>
We might not be as flashy as the bricks, but we can hold them together when nobody else can.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Dont give up when all seems lost... for its often darkest just before the dawn...
