	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Who cares who's faster or slower. I'll tell you honestly, they're ain't nothing in the land slower than a pre-29 Magician waiting for his pet to catch up due to sometimes poor AI. I know this reality as I lived it :)<BR>
<BR>
Movement speed really matters very little, except for bragging rights (which I guess matter to some), when so many factors need to be taken in to account. <BR>
<BR>
I know nothing about Bards, having come here to research the possible birth of one on my account, but even SoWing a Magician versus SoWing oneself (my second character, and now my main, is a Druid) doesn't provide measurable comparisons. <BR>
<BR>
SoW is said to be subject to the level of the player casting it, and some feel improves with age. This seems to be the concept behind many Bard songs, which only makes sense, as getting a spell and having the necessary skills to play it well are intertwined and jointly developed.<BR>
<BR>
In addition to simple run speeds, you need to add in abilities and heights of levitation effects, teleporting abilities and lag times. A Bard would likely outpace a Druid in a run from Toxxulia Forest to Steamfont, but what Druid would make this foot trip in anything but a purely academic pursuit when even prior to acquiring a surname they can cut the trip from 20 zones to 4.<BR>
<BR>
Live on confident in your ability to play your chosen class well.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
